 {"id":"jeffrey_emanuel_personal_site-5io","title":"Feature: Mobile bottom sheet for tool details","description":"# Mobile Bottom Sheet for Tool Details

## Overview
Replace inline card expansion with a bottom sheet modal on mobile devices. This provides a better mobile UX by not pushing content around and giving more room for details.

## Problem with Current Approach
- Expanding a card pushes all content below it down
- User loses context of where they were in the grid
- Expanded content is cramped in card width
- Difficult to compare tools (can only expand one at a time)

## Proposed Solution
On mobile (< 768px), clicking "Show More" opens a bottom sheet that:
- Slides up from bottom
- Contains full tool details
- Has close button and swipe-to-dismiss
- Leaves card grid visible but dimmed behind

## Design Specifications

### Bottom Sheet Anatomy
```
┌─────────────────────────────────────┐
│                                     │
│         (Dimmed backdrop)           │
│                                     │
├─────────────────────────────────────┤  ← Drag handle
│  ═══════                            │
│  [Icon] Tool Name         [✕ Close] │
│  Full tool name • ★ 1.4K            │
├─────────────────────────────────────┤
│                                     │
│  What It Does                       │
│  [Full description text]            │
│                                     │
│  Why It's Useful                    │
│  [Full explanation]                 │
│                                     │
│  Key Features                       │
│  • Feature 1                        │
│  • Feature 2                        │
│                                     │
│  [View on GitHub →]                 │
│                                     │
└─────────────────────────────────────┘
```

### Interaction States
- **Opening**: Slides up with spring physics
- **Open**: ~80% viewport height, scrollable content
- **Dismissing**: Swipe down past threshold or tap backdrop
- **Closed**: Slides down, backdrop fades

## Technical Implementation

### Using Framer Motion
```tsx
function ToolBottomSheet({ tool, isOpen, onClose }) {
  return (
    <AnimatePresence>
      {isOpen && (
        <>
          {/* Backdrop */}
          <motion.div
            initial={{ opacity: 0 }}
            animate={{ opacity: 1 }}
            exit={{ opacity: 0 }}
            onClick={onClose}
            className="fixed inset-0 bg-black/60 z-50"
          />

          {/* Sheet */}
          <motion.div
            initial={{ y: '100%' }}
            animate={{ y: 0 }}
            exit={{ y: '100%' }}
            transition={{ type: 'spring', damping: 25, stiffness: 300 }}
            drag="y"
            dragConstraints={{ top: 0, bottom: 0 }}
            dragElastic={0.2}
            onDragEnd={(_, info) => {
              if (info.offset.y > 100 || info.velocity.y > 500) {
                onClose();
              }
            }}
            className="fixed bottom-0 left-0 right-0 z-50 max-h-[85vh] rounded-t-3xl bg-slate-900 overflow-hidden"
          >
            {/* Drag handle */}
            <div className="sticky top-0 bg-slate-900 pt-3 pb-2">
              <div className="mx-auto h-1 w-12 rounded-full bg-slate-700" />
            </div>

            {/* Content */}
            <div className="overflow-y-auto px-6 pb-8">
              {/* Tool details here */}
            </div>
          </motion.div>
        </>
      )}
    </AnimatePresence>
  );
}
```

### Responsive Integration
```tsx
// In TldrToolCard
const isMobile = useMediaQuery('(max-width: 767px)');
const [sheetOpen, setSheetOpen] = useState(false);

// Different behavior based on viewport
const handleExpand = () => {
  if (isMobile) {
    setSheetOpen(true);
  } else {
    onToggleExpand?.(); // Original inline expansion
  }
};
```

## Files to Create/Modify
- `components/tool-bottom-sheet.tsx` (new) - Bottom sheet component
- `components/tldr-tool-card.tsx` - Conditional expansion behavior
- `hooks/use-media-query.ts` (if not exists) - Media query hook

## Accessibility
- Focus trap when sheet is open
- Escape key closes sheet
- `aria-modal="true"` on sheet
- Return focus to trigger button on close
- Backdrop click closes (with visual indication)

## Performance
- Lazy load sheet content (only render when opening)
- Use `will-change: transform` for smooth animation
- Portal to document.body to escape stacking contexts

## Acceptance Criteria
- [ ] Shows bottom sheet on mobile when expanding tool
- [ ] Desktop retains inline expansion behavior
- [ ] Sheet slides up with spring animation
- [ ] Swipe down to dismiss works
- [ ] Backdrop tap closes sheet
- [ ] Focus trapped inside sheet
- [ ] Escape key closes
- [ ] Content scrollable within sheet
- [ ] GitHub link accessible in sheet","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"feature","created_at":"2026-01-12T22:52:25.875281504Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-02-06T17:22:26.460230109Z","closed_at":"2026-02-06T17:22:26.460151013Z","close_reason":"Integrated mobile bottom sheet into TldrToolGrid. On mobile (<md), tool cards show compact header with 'Show Details' button that opens BottomSheet with full tool details (whatItDoes, whyItsUseful, keyFeatures, techStack, synergies). Desktop retains full inline content. Uses enhanced BottomSheet component with swipe-to-dismiss. tsc and lint pass clean.","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"jeffrey_emanuel_personal_site-5io","depends_on_id":"jeffrey_emanuel_personal_site-3zq","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-02-06T07:59:00Z","created_by":"import"},{"issue_id":"jeffrey_emanuel_personal_site-5io","depends_on_id":"jeffrey_emanuel_personal_site-7c1","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-02-06T07:59:00Z","created_by":"import"},{"issue_id":"jeffrey_emanuel_personal_site-5io","depends_on_id":"jeffrey_emanuel_personal_site-r0i","type":"child","created_at":"2026-02-06T07:59:00Z","created_by":"import"}]}
-{"id":"jeffrey_emanuel_personal_site-5s9","title":"Implement GitHub stars fetching and caching for /tldr tools","description":"# Task: GitHub Stars Fetching and Caching

## Purpose
Fetch and cache GitHub star counts for all tools to display on the /tldr page.
Stars provide social proof and should be reasonably up-to-date.

## Approach Options

### Option A: Build-Time Fetching (Recommended)
Fetch stars during build, cache in static data:
- No runtime API calls
- Fast page loads
- Stars update on each deploy
- Uses existing lib/github-stats.ts pattern

### Option B: Runtime Fetching with Cache
Fetch client-side with caching:
- Real-time star counts
- API rate limit concerns
- Additional complexity
- Loading states needed

## Implementation (Option A)

### Update build process
```typescript
// scripts/fetch-tool-stars.ts
import { Octokit } from "@octokit/rest";

const octokit = new Octokit({ auth: process.env.GITHUB_TOKEN });

const TOOL_REPOS = [
  { id: 'ntm', repo: 'Dicklesworthstone/ntm' },
  { id: 'slb', repo: 'Dicklesworthstone/simultaneous_launch_button' },
  // ... all 13 tools
];

async function fetchAllStars() {
  const stars: Record<string, number> = {};

  for (const { id, repo } of TOOL_REPOS) {
    const [owner, name] = repo.split('/');
    const { data } = await octokit.repos.get({ owner, repo: name });
    stars[id] = data.stargazers_count;
    console.log(`[STARS] ${id}: ${data.stargazers_count}`);
  }

  return stars;
}

// Write to lib/data/tldr-stars.json
```

### Update tldr-data.ts
```typescript
import starsData from './data/tldr-stars.json';

export const tldrTools: TldrTool[] = [
  {
    id: 'ntm',
    stars: starsData.ntm ?? 0,
    // ...
  }
];
```

### Build script integration
```json
{
  "scripts": {
    "prebuild": "bun run scripts/fetch-tool-stars.ts",
    "build": "next build"
  }
}
```

## Fallback Handling
```typescript
// If stars data is missing or stale, use hardcoded fallbacks
const DEFAULT_STARS: Record<string, number> = {
  'ntm': 69,
  'agent-mail': 1400,
  // ... from content.ts
};

export const getToolStars = (toolId: string): number => {
  return starsData[toolId] ?? DEFAULT_STARS[toolId] ?? 0;
};
```

## Caching Strategy
- Stars cached in JSON file
- Updated on each build
- Fallback to hardcoded values if fetch fails
- No runtime API calls

## Error Handling
```typescript
async function fetchStarsSafely() {
  try {
    return await fetchAllStars();
  } catch (error) {
    console.warn('[STARS] Failed to fetch, using cached values');
    return existingStarsData;
  }
}
```

## Acceptance Criteria
- [ ] All 13 tools have star counts
- [ ] Stars update on each deploy
- [ ] Build doesn't fail if GitHub API unavailable
- [ ] Fallback values reasonable","status":"in_progress","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-01-12T17:28:10.687009880Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-02-06T18:12:11.997888132Z","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"jeffrey_emanuel_personal_site-5s9","depends_on_id":"jeffrey_emanuel_personal_site-djw","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-02-06T07:59:00Z","created_by":"import"}]}
