## Objective
Add visible animation showing how data/messages flow between tools in the flywheel.

## Current Behavior
- Static lines connect tools
- Hover shows connection exists

## Enhanced Behavior
- Lines have subtle, continuous animation suggesting activity
- On hover, the lines TO that tool pulse more prominently
- Direction of flow is visible (arrows or particle direction)

## Animation Options

### Option A: Pulsing Lines
- Lines have a gradient that slowly moves along the path
- Simple, low-performance-cost
- Shows directionality through gradient direction

### Option B: Particle Flow
- Small dots travel along connection lines
- More visually striking but higher perf cost
- Clear directionality

### Option C: Glow Pulse
- Connections glow briefly in sequence
- Shows the "ripple" of data through the system
- Medium complexity

## Recommended: Option A (Pulsing Gradient)
- Best balance of visual impact and performance
- Works well with prefers-reduced-motion (can be static)
- Enhances existing design without overwhelming

## Implementation Notes
- Use CSS animations or Framer Motion
- Consider SVG stroke-dashoffset animation for gradient effect
- Test on mobile for performance

## Files Affected
- components/flywheel-visualization.tsx

## Dependencies
- None (can work on existing component)","status":"closed","priority":3,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2025-12-17T21:04:47.673270271Z","updated_at":"2025-12-17T23:23:01.668327319Z","closed_at":"2025-12-17T23:23:01.668327319Z","close_reason":"Implemented continuous pulsing dash animation on flywheel connection lines using stroke-dasharray/dashoffset. Animation respects prefers-reduced-motion and speeds up when highlighted.","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
