 {"id":"jeffrey_emanuel_personal_site-5w8","title":"FEATURE: Design & Build UI Components for /tldr Page","description":"# FEATURE: Design & Build UI Components for /tldr Page

## Purpose
Create the reusable React components needed for the /tldr page. These components must meet 
the highest UI/UX standards - this is a showcase page that demonstrates technical excellence.

## Components Required

### 1. TldrToolCard Component
The main card component for displaying each tool. Must include:
- Tool icon (from Lucide or custom)
- Tool name and short tagline
- Expandable/collapsible sections for:
  - "What it does" (always visible or prominent)
  - "Why it's useful"
  - "Implementation" (language, key tech)
  - "Synergies" (connected tools)
- Visual indicator of "primary" vs "supporting" tool status
- GitHub stars badge
- Link to repo
- Smooth hover states and transitions

### 2. TldrToolGrid Component
Layout component that:
- Arranges tool cards in responsive grid
- Groups by category (Primary Flywheel / Supporting Tools)
- Handles staggered entrance animations
- Maintains visual hierarchy

### 3. TldrSynergyDiagram Component
Interactive visualization showing:
- All tools as nodes
- Connections between synergistic tools
- Hover to highlight connections
- Click to filter/focus
- Animated flow lines showing data/communication paths
- Should be visually striking but not overwhelming

### 4. TldrHero Component
Page header with:
- Compelling headline about the flywheel concept
- Brief intro paragraph
- Visual element (maybe animated flywheel graphic)
- Smooth scroll to tools section

## Design Principles
- Consistent with existing site design language
- Dark theme with slate colors, gradients
- Accent colors per tool category (emerald for primary, violet for supporting, etc.)
- Generous whitespace
- Typography hierarchy
- Microinteractions on every interactive element

## Animation Requirements
- Entrance animations (staggered, spring physics)
- Hover states (scale, glow, shadow changes)
- Section expand/collapse (smooth height transitions)
- Synergy diagram (flowing particles on connections)
- Respect prefers-reduced-motion

## Accessibility
- Keyboard navigable
- ARIA labels on interactive elements
- Focus indicators
- Screen reader friendly

## Technical Notes
- Use Framer Motion for animations
- Follow existing component patterns (see endorsement-card.tsx, project-card.tsx)
- Memoize where appropriate
- Lazy load heavy components","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"feature","created_at":"2026-01-12T17:13:32.193901182Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-01-12T19:46:13.036333859Z","closed_at":"2026-01-12T19:46:13.036333859Z","close_reason":"Completed - TLDR page fully implemented with all components and navigation","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"jeffrey_emanuel_personal_site-5w8","depends_on_id":"jeffrey_emanuel_personal_site-1lj","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-02-06T07:59:00Z","created_by":"import"},{"issue_id":"jeffrey_emanuel_personal_site-5w8","depends_on_id":"jeffrey_emanuel_personal_site-8uk","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-02-06T07:59:00Z","created_by":"import"},{"issue_id":"jeffrey_emanuel_personal_site-5w8","depends_on_id":"jeffrey_emanuel_personal_site-gy1","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-02-06T07:59:00Z","created_by":"import"},{"issue_id":"jeffrey_emanuel_personal_site-5w8","depends_on_id":"jeffrey_emanuel_personal_site-uv7","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-02-06T07:59:00Z","created_by":"import"},{"issue_id":"jeffrey_emanuel_personal_site-5w8","depends_on_id":"jeffrey_emanuel_personal_site-uw1","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-02-06T07:59:00Z","created_by":"import"},{"issue_id":"jeffrey_emanuel_personal_site-5w8","depends_on_id":"jeffrey_emanuel_personal_site-wsp","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-02-06T07:59:00Z","created_by":"import"}]}
